  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 12 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 4 critical, 6 high, 18 medium, 11 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK), Tirana International Airport Mother Teresa (TIA/LATI) and Belgrade Nikola Tesla (BEG/LYBE); plus 7 other bases. 18 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, low cloud base and RVR limitations  — most notably around Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP), Bucharest Băneasa Aurel Vlaicu (BBU/LRBS) and Belgrade Nikola Tesla (BEG/LYBE). Network hotspots: Bucharest Băneasa Aurel Vlaicu (BBU/LRBS), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP), Billund (BLL/EKBI), Copenhagen Kastrup (CPH/EKCH), Ålesund Airport, Vigra (AES/ENAL) and 7 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and very low visibility. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Billund (BLL/EKBI), Copenhagen Kastrup (CPH/EKCH), Ålesund Airport, Vigra (AES/ENAL) and 9 others.",
